SABRE PV Flag Issue

Many AMCST books currently have SABRE PV = Yes, which is considered a data quality problem — nobody confirmed or requested this; some of these books may have originally been fair value and later reclassified to amortised cost
Aspire currently ignores AMCST books where SABRE PV = No — so there is no downstream impact today
Once project goes live, recommendation: flip all AMCST books to SABRE PV = Yes at go-live (purely operational step, no project impact)
DMV / clean PV numbers will be affected when the flag toggles — concern raised by Mengxi, to be revisited on next call


Feed Architecture (Current State)

Today: Feeds go directly to Aspire and to PCQ (because full FMRP hasn't happened yet)
Strategic state: RATAN is the single feed → distributes to Aspire; direct Murex feed stops
This project does not change the feed architecture — direct-to-Aspire continues for now
For fair value books: Aspire already consumes SABRE PV; accruals are not sent separately (full PV only), except for two products — RKS Secured Loan and CDS Guarantee — where accruals are sent separately from Murex
For AMCST books: the goal of this project is to onboard SABRE accrual numbers into Aspire, substituting Murex


PLVA / PCQ File Discussion

Downstream PLVA files currently carry full Murex PV (including for AMCST books) — this is legacy behaviour
The PLVA is not trade-level — it is highly granular. One trade can produce multiple rows due to:

Risk factor breakdowns
Mid-life amendments
Rate fixings (i.e. each floating rate observation/lock-in event on instruments such as floating rate swaps generates its own record)


PCQ receives several file types from SABRE:

Explained files — cumulative risk factor level P&L explain
Market ops file — together with explained files, fully explains results
PV file — trade/sub-library level PV of today (this is where columns could potentially be added)
Additional file specific to BTS (Puneet's request)


The MIS report (managed by the cascade team / Steve's team) consumes PLVA data from PCQ and uses the full PV — for AMCST books it then rewrites/overlays with accruals on top. This is legacy Murex behaviour.
Question raised: can feeds be changed to carry accrued interest only (not full PV) for AMCST books, since accrued interest is a trade-level property and the MIS/PC Credit only needs accruals for these books?
SABRE can potentially add an accrued interest column to the trade-level PV file sent to PCQ — needs exploration
First need to confirm whether the PLVA consumed downstream is actually sourced from the PCQ PV file


